## Closing Statement

STOCRS-R explores a simple but fundamental idea:

Application correctness emerges deterministically from structure — without requiring procedural sequencing as the source of correctness.

Execution may reveal output.  
Structure determines admissibility.

It is released to encourage:

- independent validation  
- real-world testing  
- safe experimentation  

STOCRS-R is offered as a minimal, verifiable reference implementation of that possibility.
